        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> <BR> Looks like there is a site up now to hire, for multi-kpp, a crew of manaburners to waste whatever mob you need dead.. epic mob, dragon haste, etc, if it can be MB'd to death looks like they'll do it.<BR>Link is on mobhunter.com, here are their "rules"...</P><P>..now, I don't have a problem with manaburn, except maybe in PvP as a free one-shot kill every 2 hours is kinda cheap, but jesus... this is really waving their dicks in VI's face. I smell nerfage if they keep this up, despite VI's statement of non-MB-nerfage.</P><P></P><P>RULES AND POLICIES</P><P>1. FFA MOBS. We consider every FFA mob to be a race mob, and therefore will freely manaburn them as soon as we get the required number of wizards, even if there is already a guild gathering to take the said mob down. We will not, however, KS a mob if any guild is already engaging it. We do not hold any objections against manaburning a mob after a guild is wiped out, however.</P><P>2. ROTATION MOBS. We are not really a guild, so are unable to join rotations for mobs. But, we feel that we also deserve a chance against those mobs. Therefore, we WILL engage any rotation mob just as any FFA mob, with a single exception: if a guild is already gathering to take down a rotation mob, we will not interfere. Other than that, we will take out any rotation mob at any avaliable opportunity.</P><P>3. DISCRETION. Every member of the Manaburn Sindicate is expected to attend raids with /anon turned on. This rule was made so that we are not subject to the flaming and shitty comments from whiners that we would otherwise have to endure. It also prevents said whiners from trying to spread a bad reputation against our guilds using the manaburn sindicate as an argument.</P><P>4. KSing. We will not, in any occasion, KS any mobs. Unless, of course, we are paid well enough : P</P><P>5. LOOT. All loot will be handled by the loot masters. The LM will have the job of recording the people attending each raid, selling the loot, and distributing the plat between the people that attended said raid. If any wizard wishes to have a piece of loot for himself rather than having it sold, he should contact the LM before the raid. If you are interested in buying some loot, please visit the Hitlist and Prices page.</P><P>6. MEMBERSHIP. To apply to membership, simply send an email to <a href="mailto:manaburn@hotmail.com.">manaburn@hotmail.com.</a> If you are found to be indeed a real manaburner with a real interest in joining, we will contact you.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34033" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34033</a></font></td>

